Domain of complex logarithm of (s+a)/(s+b) = { s ∈ ℂ | (s+a)/(s+b) ≠ 0, Re[(s+a)/(s+b)] >0}

In addition, since the complex logarithm is a multi-valued function, the domain may need to be further specified depending on precisely how we choose a branch of the logarithm. Specifically, the domain may need to be restricted to avoid branch cuts, which are the discontinuities in the value of the logarithm due to the multi-valuedness of the function.
